'''''World Class Baseball''''' is a [[baseball]] video game originally released by [[Hudson Soft]] for the [[NEC]] [[TurboGrafx-16|PC Engine]] in 1988 in Japan, and the TurboGrafx-16 in 1989 in North America. It was ported to the [[X68000|Sharp X68000]] that same year and it was only released in Japan. It was re-released for the [[Wii]] [[Virtual Console]] service in [[North America]] on September 17, 2007, and in [[PAL]] regions on September 21, 2007.

== Gameplay ==
''World Class Baseball'' features 12 teams that must be defeated in the single player Pennant Mode, a knockout competition. Upon defeating all teams, the player faces off against the Turbo Tigers, a non-player selectable team of all-stars. The game also gives the option for players to compete in a one or two player versus exhibition game, or to watch two computer controlled teams play each other.

